morning_weapon:
    clear_dialog
    set_stat day 4
    set_stat actions 6
    run transition_instant generic_wake

    stop music
    play sound doorknock
    "KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "There is a knocking at your front door. It's not a friendly knocking. The <span class='goldItalic'>golden light</span> is vaporised by the 'you are about to have to talk to someone at 9AM' adrenaline rush."
        "*More* knocking!?":
            talk orb talk "Apparently so."
            clear_dialog
            talk lovely talk "Good morning, Ghost!"
            choice:
                talk nasty talk "Morning, cunts."
                "Good morning little ladies. Orb.":
                    talk orb talk "Yes. It is morning isn't it."
        "I knew it. A third visitor. I'm so smart. [Pat yourself on the back] Tomorrow I predict a *fourth*." if $data.ghost.predictedThirdVisitor:
            talk nasty talk "Good call. Always keep betting. Never back out. That's how you win *big*."
        "I knew it. A third visitor. I'm so smart. [Pat yourself on the back] I'm not going to push my luck by predicting a *fourth*, though." if $data.ghost.predictedThirdVisitor:
            run skip
    clear_dialog
    if (!= (quest_succeeded? fixHouse) true):
        "Your room is so cold. Your nipples could cut through glass. Winter is closer every day. This roof really ought to be fixed soon..."
        clear_dialog
        talk poppy talk "The game keeps telling you that if you don't fix the roof you will catch your death of cold AND YET it is STILL not fixed what more handholding do you need!?"
        clear_dialog
        talk poppy talk "PLAYER."
        talk poppy talk "FIX."
        talk poppy talk "GHOST'S."
        talk poppy talk "FUCKING."
        talk poppy talk "ROOF."
        start_objective fixHouse fixHouseUrgent
        clear_dialog
    if $data.ghost.sawComet:
        talk lovely talk "One was hoping for a lie in tonight, yesterday evening was rather tiring!"
        talk orb talk "Having to keep quiet for more than a few seconds is tiring for you, is it? That explains a lot."
        talk nasty talk "Eheh. Oh she wasn't quiet last night! Whine whine whine. You homos should go look at the sky more often, eh?"
        talk lovely talk "H- hey! Don't tell those two about... about... what happened last night! My honour is at stake!"
        clear_dialog
        talk nasty talk "No honour in <span class='writtenText'>'what happened last night'</span>, fucken hel."
        clear_dialog
    play sound doorknock
    choice:
        "Knock knock. Endless knocking. This is just how you're going to wake up every morning now, it seems."
        "[Get dressed, and then go downstairs and open the front door]":
            play sound dooropen
            play music chilling
            if (objective_started? houseSnake boneman):
                jump ending_boneman
            else:
                run transition morning_weapon
                talk weapon talk "You seen my sheep?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "In a somewhat surprising twist, the worlds least sociable shepherd has decided to come speak to you. Or speak at you, at least."
        "\\"Please don't kill me! I'm sorry I tried to steal that plank off of you!\\" [Drop to your knees, clasp your hands together, and wait for the end]" if $data.weapon.redHanded: 
            play sound thud
            "You can't see it on account of their eyepatch, but The Weapon rolls their missing eye."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk weapon talk "Look, I'm not going to kill you. I don't care about you. Just... be normal and don't steal any more of my things, got it?"
                "\\"Oh. Okay. I'll be normal now.\\" [Stand back up] \\"How can I help you today, friend?\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"Oh. Okay. I'll be normal now.\\" [Stand back up, a little disappointed not to be dead] \\"How can I help you today, friend?\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"Oh. Okay. I can't promise I'll be normal but I'll stop stealing your things.\\" [Stand back up] \\"How can I help you today, friend?\\"":
                    run skip
        "\\"What?\\"" if (!= $data.weapon.redHanded true):
            run skip
        "\\"Good morning to you too!\\" [Do a gay little wave]" if (!= $data.weapon.redHanded true):
            run skip
    talk weapon talk "I said <span class='writtenText'>'You seen my sheep?'</span> It was a question."
    if (roll morning_weapon_missing_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "I think they're missing a sheep."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk weapon talk "Probably hopped over the fence in search of a snack and got herself lost in the woods, the silly thing. You happen to see her you let me know, mhm?"
        "\\"Is this a quest?\\"":
            choice:
                talk weapon talk "A quest? No. I'm just asking you to tell me if you see an escaped sheep around anywhere. Hardly a Grecian epic, is it?"
                "[Nod and awkwardly mumble to yourself] \\"It's a quest...\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"I fully intend to make it one. I shall track down this stray beast!\\"":
                    talk weapon talk "Mhm. Fine. I won't stop you."
            clear_dialog
            run transition generic_chivalry
            talk nasty talk "A quest huh? Fuck me, you've got my latent 'Dame Most Chivalrous' instincts going, which I guess makes the sheep my 'Ladie Most Lovelie'."
            talk lovely talk "Ahem, I think you'll find *I* am your 'Ladie Most Lovelie', Nasty Girl! Not some wool brained beastie!"
            if $data.ghost.sawComet:
                talk nasty talk "You're mine huh? And to think you were acting oh so bashful about the two of us just a few moments ago..."
                talk lovely talk "!!!"
                clear_dialog
                talk lovely talk "K- kill yourself you... you... you fiend!"
            else:
                talk nasty talk "You're mine huh? Verily."
                talk lovely talk "..."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Ignoring Nasty Girl and Lovely Lady's weird sexual tension for a moment, we should probably find out a little about this sheep before we go blindly gallivanting off in search of it."
            clear_dialog
            run transition morning_weapon
    clear_dialog
    play sound thud
    choice:
        "You pull out your trusty notebook, drop it on the floor, pick it back up, and flip it open."
        "\\"Does your escaped sheep have a name?\\"":
            choice:
                talk weapon talk "Her name's Parsnip."
                "[Jot <span class='writtenText'>'Parsnip'</span> down in your notes]":
                    play sound write
                    talk weapon talk "Her sister's called Carrot. Not that that matters."
                "[Jot <span class='writtenText'>'Parsnip'</span> down in your notes] \\"And does Parsnip have a surname?\\"":
                    play sound write
                    choice:
                        talk weapon talk "She's a sheep."
                        "\\"Oh. Of course. Sheep don't have surnames. Silly me.\\"":
                            talk weapon talk "Mhm. They don't."
                        "\\"Don't worry friend, she has one now.\\" [Jot <span class='writtenText'>'Parsnip Parsnipy'</span> down in your notebook]" if $data.ghost.nameGhosty:
                            play sound write
                            "The Weapon watches you jot down the phrase <span class='writtenText'>'Parsnip Parsnipy'</span>. Their eye narrows. They regret knocking on your door."
                        "[Jot <span class='writtenText'>'She's a sheep'</span> down in your notes]":
                            play sound write
                            "The Weapon watches you jot down the phrase <span class='writtenText'>'she's a sheep'</span>. Their eye narrows. They regret knocking on your door."
            jump morning_weapon_menu

morning_weapon_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Weapon sniffs the air. A queer miasma in the air... probably you."
        "\\"Has your escaped sheep ever been an escaped sheep before?\\"":
            choice:
                talk weapon talk "...Eh?"
                "\\"Has Parsnip ever escaped before?\\"":
                    talk weapon talk "No. She's always been too dim. Probably fell out the field by accident that one. Her sister Carrot has a few times though. Scuffled her way under the fence. Found her a day later wandering around the edge of the woods."
            jump morning_weapon_menu
        "\\"Is there a bounty on Parsnips head?\\" [Lean in and whisper] \\"I'm asking if you'll give me money.\\"" if (! $data.morning_weapon_feeDecided):
            set data.morning_weapon_feeDecided true
            talk weapon talk "Aye. I'll pay you a finders fee. Assuming you find her, that is."
            if $data.weapon.redHanded: 
                set data.weapon.findersFee 5
                choice:
                    talk weapon talk "Five Pounds and I'll forget you ever tried to rob me. Deal?"
                    "[Shake their hand] \\"Deal!\\"":
                        "They shake your limp wristed little hand."
            else:
                if (roll morning_weapon_menu_price_nasty nasty 40):
                    choice:
                        talk nasty talk "Here's your chance. If you're good at something, always charge what your labour is owed."
                        "Am I good at finding sheep?":
                            talk nasty talk "Fuck if I know, but you should set your price now anyway."
                            clear_dialog
                            choice:
                                "The Weapon snorts. Their nose is blocked. Gross."
                                "\\"One sheep coming right up. That'll be ten trillion pounds please.\\" [Hold out your hand to make a deal]":
                                    "You make your 'I am normal and can be trusted with disposable income' face a little too eager. The Weapon frowns."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk weapon talk "I'll pay you twenty pounds. End of. I'm a shepherd, not a kaiser."
                                    set data.weapon.finderFee 20
                                    clear_dialog
                                    choice:
                                        talk nasty talk "Idiot. I told you to charge your worth, not to demand more money than there is in the fucking universe."
                                        "I don't even know my own name! How am I supposed to know we aren't undergoing hyperinflation???":
                                            talk orb talk "Read a newspaper. Go to the shop and look at the prices. Ask the omniscient Orb that lives in your chest. The list goes on really."
                                "\\"Thirty-five pounds is my going rate for sheep snatching.\\" [Hold out your hand to make a deal]":
                                    set data.weapon.finderFee 35
                                    "The Weapon hesitates for a moment. They squint at you, searching your soul. Snipers can see those."
                                    if (roll morning_weapon_menu_type_lovely lovely 40):
                                        talk lovely talk "They're trying to divine whether or not you seem the sort who could find a missing sheep. They're annoyed that you are."
                                    else:
                                        wait 1000
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk weapon talk "Deal."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    "They shake your limp wristed little hand."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    choice:
                                        talk nasty talk "We'll make a handylady out of you yet, Ghost. We'll fix so many boilers together."
                                        "We don't need training to do that?":
                                            talk nasty talk "Fuck no. Plumbing's easy, it's like fucking... those toys you give kids with the beads on the wires to keep em busy at the doctors, innit?"
                                            if (roll morning_weapon_menu_plumbing_orb orb 20):
                                                talk orb talk "It is not like that."
                                            talk lovely talk "Ravensbridge manor had a room sized one of those when I was a little girl... sigh... oh how I long for those halcyon days..."
                                "\\"Twenty Pounds is my going rate for sheep snatching.\\" [Hold out your hand to make a deal]":
                                    set data.weapon.finderFee 20
                                    talk weapon talk "Deal."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    "They shake your limp wristed little hand."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk nasty talk "Argh! Ghost! You undersold yourself! I'm beginning to have second thoughts about going into the 'mate you hire to fix your radiator' business with you!"
                                "\\"Eh, I'll do it for free. I'm a communist.\\"":
                                    set data.weapon.finderFee 0
                                    "The Weapon's brow furrows."
                                    clear_dialog
                                    talk weapon talk "Fine."
                                    if (roll morning_weapon_menu_communist_lovely lovely 20):
                                        talk lovely talk "They aren't wholly pleased to be going into business with a self-proclaimed communist, but if it means they don't have to pay you they're willing to accept. Papi would be *so* proud."
                                    else:
                                        wait 1000
                else:
                    set data.weapon.finderFee 20
                    choice:
                        talk weapon talk "Twenty Pounds. Deal?"
                        "[Shake their hand] \\"Deal!\\"":
                            "They shake your limp wristed little hand."
            jump morning_weapon_menu
        "\\"Does Parsnip have any special skills?\\"":
            talk weapon talk "Aye. Strong nose, and stronger still taste for Oestromoss. Was thinking about training her for some of those Sheep shows they do now, but the boss said t'was a waste of time."
            if (roll morning_weapon_menu_oestromoss_orb orb 60):
                talk orb talk "Oestromoss grows quite commonly in the woods here, and across Anglia more broadly. It's not edible on it's own, but some very talented botanists use it to create moonshine Oestrogen. Sheep like to gnaw on it though, it tastes sweet to them. Some farmers use sheep to hunt for it, similar to truffles."
                talk lovely talk "Truggles! Yim yam!"
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump morning_weapon_menu
        "\\"When did you last see Parsnip?\\"":
            talk weapon talk "Last night. Put all the sheep to bed. Tucked 'em in."
            if (roll morning_weapon_menu_joke_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "Despite what their complete absence of a facial expression might suggest, that was them attempting a 'joke'."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk weapon talk "Must have escaped during the night, maybe early morning. Very early morning. I'm usually at my station by about 4AM."
            if (roll morning_weapon_menu_4am_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "You can count the number of times you've willingly gotten out of bed before 6AM on one hand."
            else:
                wait 1000
            if (roll morning_weapon_menu_station_lovely lovely 60):
                talk lovely talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Station'.</span> They still call it that. Their eyeball may have left them, but their training didn't."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump morning_weapon_menu
        "\\"What should I do when I find her?\\"":
            talk weapon talk "Just call her over. Maybe lure her in with some food. She'll follow you home. Sheep don't like being lost anymore than you do."
            jump morning_weapon_menu
        "\\"That's all I need to know. My quest begins at once. I swear this to thee, I shall't not return to thy field till Parsnip lyeth in mine hands!\\" <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            start_quest weapon
            start_objective weapon parsnip
            talk weapon talk "Mhm."
            clear_dialog
            play sound footsteps
            run transition generic_door
            "The Weapon turns and wanders off, apparently unimpressed by your commitment to making this a quest. They soon disappear down the lane, leaving you cold and alone at your door."
            clear_dialog
            talk lovely talk "Wheee! How exciting!"
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "Finally, a quest worthy of a Dame Most Chivalrous! Awoooo!"
        "Awooooooooooo! <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            talk nasty talk "Awoooooo!"
            talk lovely talk "A quest! A quest! Wheeeeee!"
            clear_dialog
            set_screen day_four
            play sound sting_day
            wait 8000
            jump goToGameMap